# No em dashes in website copy

Do not use the em dash character (`—`, U+2014) in user-facing text.

This applies to UI strings, placeholders, metadata descriptions, markdown served to users (e.g. privacy policy), and empty-state/table placeholders visible in the product.

**Use instead:**

- A period to start a new sentence
- A comma for a light pause
- A colon before a list or clarification
- Parentheses for asides

```tsx
// ❌ BAD
"Kurator is your personal collection tracker — organize games…"
"None — choose when you obtain each item"

// ✅ GOOD
"Kurator is your personal collection tracker. Organize games…"
"None (choose when you obtain each item)"
```

Code comments and developer-only JSDoc are not website copy; still avoid em dashes in strings shown to users.
